## Spec-driven development

This codebase uses a spec-driven development framework. When generating
Angular components or patterns, always check for a relevant spec before
writing code.

### Finding a spec

Check the registry for active specs:
- Registry index: `tools/registry/registry.json`
- Run: `node tools/registry/registry-cli.js search "<use case>"`
- Pattern specs: `specs/ds/patterns/*.spec.md`
- Token adapter: `specs/ds/tokens/semantic.spec.md`
- Component map: `specs/ds/components/component-map.spec.md`

If an active spec exists: follow it completely.
If no spec exists: apply Angular conventions below and note the gap.

### Reading a spec — required steps

Read in this order before writing any code:

1. **§2 Scope** — confirm in scope; if not, name the correct spec
2. **§3 Tokens** — every visual property uses semantic tokens only
3. **§4 Structure** — generate file scaffold first
4. **§5 Config** — copy verbatim, no modifications
5. **§6 Types** — DS renderers and formatters only, no inline logic
6. **§7 Variants** — identify and state the correct variant
7. **§8–9 States** — loading, empty, and error are all required
8. **§11 Checklist** — self-verify, report results before code

### Output contract

Output this before any generated code:

```
<!-- SPEC COMPLIANCE REPORT -->
Spec: [spec-id] v[version]
Variant: [name] — [reason]
Checklist: [§11 items: ✓ / ✗ / ⚠]
Unresolved: [independent decisions made]
```

### Angular 19 conventions (always apply)

```typescript
// Use signals API
name    = input<string>();
value   = input.required<number>();
changed = output<void>();
service = inject(MyService);

// Never use
@Input() @Output() constructor(private ...)
```

- Standalone components — no NgModules
- `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` always
- `takeUntilDestroyed()` for all subscriptions
- DS wrapper components only — no direct Material/AG Grid imports
- Semantic SCSS tokens only — no raw values, no inline styles

### Token imports (always stable)

```scss
@use '@company/spec-tokens/color'   as color;
@use '@company/spec-tokens/type'    as type;
@use '@company/spec-tokens/spacing' as spacing;
@use '@company/spec-tokens/grid'    as grid-tokens;
```

### Deprecated specs

Stop immediately if `status: deprecated`. Use `deprecatedBy` spec instead.

